<div id="so_formfield_dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_" class="field fld_description fld-ro">

            <div class="label" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__field-label">
	<label for="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description_">Synopsis</label><span class="req-indicator"></span>:
      </div>
            
      	 	<div class="widget" id="dnf_class_values_procurement_notice__description__widget">
			<div class="notice_desc_dates">
				<span class="added">Added: <input type="hidden" name="dnf_class_values[procurement_notice][description][0][added_on]" value="2014-02-11 14:56:53">Feb 11, 2014 2:56 pm</span>
					</div>
		The Department of Navy (DON) Space and Naval Warfare Systems Command<br /><br /> (SPAWAR) Program Executive Office for<br /><br /> Enterprise Information Systems (PEO-<br /><br /> EIS) has identified a potential<br /><br /> requirement for an Enterprise Service<br /><br /> Bus (ESB) capability to replace the<br /><br /> current core infrastructure and adapter<br /><br /> of the Standard Procurement System<br /><br /> (SPS).  The adapter provides<br /><br /> messaging and mediation services<br /><br /> required for system-to-system financial<br /><br /> transactions between DON Business<br /><br /> Systems.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> As a result, SPAWAR PEO-EIS is<br /><br /> seeking information regarding the<br /><br /> potential of the market to support<br /><br /> providing an ESB capability. The<br /><br /> information gathered through this<br /><br /> RFI/Market Survey process will help<br /><br /> influence future product investments<br /><br /> and support in the DON.  Additional<br /><br /> information regarding this RFI,<br /><br /> including specifically requested<br /><br /> information, can be within the attached<br /><br /> RFI document.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> All information contained in this RFI is<br /><br /> preliminary, subject to modification,<br /><br /> and is not binding on the Government.<br /><br /> The information requested may be<br /><br /> used to facilitate decision-making and<br /><br /> will not be disclosed outside the<br /><br /> agency.  Any determination of a<br /><br /> subsequent procurement strategy is<br /><br /> solely within the discretion of the<br /><br /> Government.  The DON, SPAWAR, and<br /><br /> PEO-EIS may, as a result of the<br /><br /> information provided, invite individual<br /><br /> vendors to participate in a<br /><br /> separate Industry Day events to<br /><br /> further demonstrate the capabilities of<br /><br /> their specific system.   However,<br /><br /> participation at an Industry Day will<br /><br /> be by invitation only, and will require<br /><br /> additional data submissions, if<br /><br /> requested.  No decision whether to hold<br /><br /> an "Industry Day" has been made, and<br /><br /> will in part be a decision based on the<br /><br /> response to this RFI.<br /><br /> <br /><br /> THIS IS A REQUEST FOR INFORMATION<br /><br /> (RFI) ONLY. This RFI is issued solely<br /><br /> for information and planning<br /><br /> purposes  it does not constitute a<br /><br /> Request for Proposal (RFP) or a<br /><br /> promise to issue an RFP in the future.<br /><br /> This request for information does not<br /><br /> commit the Government to contract for<br /><br /> any supply or service that may stem<br /><br /> from this RFI.  Respondents are<br /><br /> advised that the Government will not<br /><br /> pay for any information or<br /><br /> administrative costs incurred in<br /><br /> response to this RFI; all costs<br /><br /> associated with responding to this RFI<br /><br /> will be solely at the interested partys<br /><br /> expense.  Small Businesses having the<br /><br /> capabilities to perform the tasking<br /><br /> below are encouraged to reply to this<br /><br /> RFI.  Not responding to this RFI does<br /><br /> not preclude participation in any future<br /><br /> RFP, if any is issued.  If an RFP is<br /><br /> issued, it will be synopsized on the<br /><br /> Federal Business Opportunities<br /><br /> (FedBizOpps) website at<br /><br /> http://www.fbo.gov.  It is the<br /><br /> responsibility of potential offerors to<br /><br /> monitor these sites for additional<br /><br /> information pertaining to this<br /><br /> requirement.


	</div><!-- widget -->
	
        </div><!--field ( Synopsis )-->

		

